tokenize(text)

Tokenizes a piece of text into its word pieces. This uses a greedy longest-match-first algorithm to perform tokenization using the given vocabulary. For example:

input = “unaffable” output = [“un”, “##aff”, “##able”]

Parameters:

text – A single token or whitespace separated tokens. This should have already been passed through `BasicTokenizer.

Returns:

A list of wordpiece tokens.
